<subSubSection id="C32007A4E31D4B47FEE4F927FDBBF8AC" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B85542FE31D4B47FEE4F927FB5EF8DC" blockId="5.[264,1324,1233,1899]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<emphasis id="B94E883DE31D4B47FEE4F927FE72F90C" bold="true" box="[312,426,1713,1739]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Remarks</emphasis>
: 
<taxonomicName id="4C3A2FACE31D4B47FE65F924FCDAF90C" box="[441,770,1714,1739]" class="Malacostraca" family="Corophiidae" genus="Monocorophium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="insidiosum">
<emphasis id="B94E883DE31D4B47FE65F924FCDAF90C" box="[441,770,1714,1739]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Monocorophium insidiosum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is associated with 
<taxonomicName id="4C3A2FACE31D4B47FC01F924FB92F90C" box="[989,1098,1714,1739]" class="Liliopsida" family="Cymodoceaceae" genus="Halodule" kingdom="Plantae" order="Alismatales" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B94E883DE31D4B47FC01F924FB92F90C" box="[989,1098,1714,1739]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Halodule</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C3A2FACE31D4B47FB5EF924FB2CF90C" box="[1154,1268,1714,1739]" class="Liliopsida" family="Hydrocharitaceae" genus="Thalassia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Alismatales" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B94E883DE31D4B47FB5EF924FB2CF90C" box="[1154,1268,1714,1739]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Thalassia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
seagrasses, and algal beds (
<bibRefCitation id="EFAB29DEE31D4B47FDFFF94FFD0CF934" author="Ledoyer" box="[547,724,1753,1779]" pageId="5" pageNumber="14" refString="Ledoyer, M. (1986) Fauna Mobile des Herviers de Phanerogames marines (Halodule et Thaalassia) de la Laguna de Terminos (Mexique, Campeche) II. Les Gammariens (Crustacea). Anales del Instituto de Ciencias del Mar y Limnologia, 13 (3), 171 - 200." type="journal article" year="1986">
Ledoyer, 
<number id="3DF24608E31D4B47FD49F94FFD0CF934" box="[661,724,1753,1779]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="1986.0">1986</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). Apparently, 
<taxonomicName id="4C3A2FACE31D4B47FCA4F94CFBC7F934" box="[888,1055,1754,1779]" class="Malacostraca" family="Corophiidae" genus="Monocorophium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="insidiosum">
<emphasis id="B94E883DE31D4B47FCA4F94CFBC7F934" box="[888,1055,1754,1779]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">M. insidiosum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a widely distributed species that has been transported to different world regions (
<bibRefCitation id="EFAB29DEE31D4B47FC17F897FBA1F8DC" author="Barnard" box="[971,1145,1793,1819]" pageId="5" pageNumber="13" refString="Barnard, J. L. (1970) Sublittoral Gammaridea (Amphipoda) of the Hawaiian Islands. Smithsonian Contributions to Zoology 34, 1 - 286." type="journal article" year="1970">
Barnard, 
<number id="3DF24608E31D4B47FBE6F897FBA1F8DC" box="[1082,1145,1793,1819]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="1970.0">1970</number>
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B85542FE31D4B47FEE4F8BFFDBBF8AC" blockId="5.[264,1324,1233,1899]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
The salinity and temperature ranges measured at the collection site were 
<number id="3DF24608E31D4B47FB41F8BFFB27F884" box="[1181,1279,1833,1859]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="25.0" valueMax="26.0" valueMin="24.0">24 to 26</number>
%o and 
<number id="3DF24608E31D4B47FEE6F8C7FE41F8AC" box="[314,409,1873,1899]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="27.5" valueMax="28.0" valueMin="27.0">27 to 28</number>
°C, respectively.
</paragraph>
